{"abstract": "Tech firms may find no-poaching pacts costly. | Guy Hands appears to have a green thumb. | SAC Capital Advisors quietly rechristens itself Point72 Asset Management. | Equity fund buys matzo maker.", "web_url": "https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/04/08/morning-agenda-questioning-the-valleys-no-poaching-pacts/", "snippet": "Tech firms may find no-poaching pacts costly. | Guy Hands appears to have a green thumb. | SAC Capital Advisors quietly rechristens itself Point72 Asset Management. | Equity fund buys matzo maker.", "lead_paragraph": "\u201cA high-stakes negotiation is taking place in Silicon Valley among some of the biggest names in the industry \u2014 Apple and Google among them \u2014 over accusations that they were involved in a collusion to prevent their employees from being hired at rival companies,\u201d Andrew Ross Sorkin writes in the DealBook column. {"abstract": "A self-driving car being tested by Google struck a public bus on a city street in Mountain View, Calif.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/01/technology/autonomous-google-car-hits-public-bus-during-test-drive.html", "snippet": "A self-driving car being tested by Google struck a public bus on a city street in Mountain View, Calif.", "lead_paragraph": "A self-driving car being tested by Google struck a public bus on a city street in Mountain View, Calif. The tech company\u2019s vehicles have been involved in more than a dozen minor accidents, but this fender-bender may represent the first time that a Google car has caused an accident. A report from Google on the Feb. 14 episode was posted online Monday by California\u2019s Department of Motor Vehicles. Google\u2019s car was moving at less than two miles an hour and the bus at 15 m.p.h. No one was injured. The report does not address fault, but Google wrote that its car was trying to get around some sandbags when its left front struck the right side of the bus. Google did not have immediate comment. {"abstract": "The Verizon boss, Lowell McAdam, is betting the deal will help attract digital advertisers by meshing Yahoo with AOL, which Verizon bought last year.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/26/business/dealbook/verizon-and-yahoo-internet-also-rans-with-big-hopes.html", "snippet": "The Verizon boss, Lowell McAdam, is betting the deal will help attract digital advertisers by meshing Yahoo with AOL, which Verizon bought last year.", "lead_paragraph": "Verizon is continuing to invest in ancient web history.
